# SolidWorks API MCP Server

This project includes an MCP server (`user-SolidWorks-API`) with tools to query SolidWorks API documentation.

## Available Tools

Use `CallMcpTool` with `server: "user-SolidWorks-API"` and these tool names:

| Tool | Purpose | Required Parameters |
|------|---------|---------------------|
| `search_solidworks_api` | Search API docs | `query` (string) |
| `get_method_details` | Get method/property details | `interface_name`, `method_name` |
| `get_interface_details` | Get full interface info | `interface_name` |
| `search_programming_guides` | Search guides/examples | `query` (string) |

## Example Calls

```json
// Search for API methods
{"query": "AddConfiguration2", "limit": 5}

// Get method details
{"interface_name": "IConfigurationManager", "method_name": "AddConfiguration2"}

// Get interface overview
{"interface_name": "IModelDoc2"}
```

## When to Use

- User asks about SolidWorks API methods or interfaces
- Reviewing/writing VBA macros or C# add-ins
- Validating API parameter order and types
- Finding code examples and best practices
